HEADWORD: Liniment
<hw>Lin"i*ment</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n"⟦icr⟧*m⟦eit⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>linimentum</ets>, fr. <ets>linire</ets>,
<ets>linere</ets>, to besmear, anoint : cf. F. <ets>liniment</ets>. Cf.
<er>Letter</er>, <er>Lime</er> a viscous substance.]</ety> <def>A liquid
or semiliquid preparation of a consistence thinner than an ointment,
applied to the skin by friction, esp. one used as a sedative or a
stimulant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

